column2: When I attempt to enter the temperatures for this date- the form flips to a date in 2002 and I am unable to enter them- so here they are for:  3' - 71.4- 6' - 70.8- 9' - 70.5- 12' - 69.8- 15' - 68.9  Secchi depth is 4'.  For some reason the site does not allow me to enter the secchi data for this date.
Bay is murky with iron floc.
Sunny- warm.  No water coming in from marsh.
Merganser duck family in bay.  No water coming in from marsh.
Beautiful- sunny.  Sampled with Sandy Wickman of DNR - she showed us collection techniques.
SOUTH BAY BY INLET - INTEGRATED SAMPLE
Sunny- light wind.  First sample after our 6+ inches of rain 5 days ago.
First time on the lake this year.  Moderate wind.
Perfect day to sample.  No iron floc coming in from the Powell Marsh.
Light chop.  Sunny.  No water coming in from marsh.
Slightly overcast.  No water coming in from Powell Marsh.
Sunny.  Beautiful day.  No water coming in from Powell Marsh.
Sunny.  Checking Secchi at the request of Jim Kreitlow of DNR.
Checking Secchi at the request of Jim Kreitlow of DNR.
Sunny- no water coming in from Powell Marsh.  1" of rain 2 days ago.
Sunny.  Cool.  Small amount of water entering from Powell Marsh ditches.
First day in June that was both sunny and calm.  No rain.  No water from Powell Marsh.
Sunny- calm.  Powell Marsh ditches loaded with iron floc.
Sunny.  Light wind.  Beginning to see iron floc coming into bay from Powell Marsh inlet.
Sunny- calm.  Little rain all summer (less than 1/2").  No water coming in from Powell Marsh.
No water coming in from Powell Marsh.  Water VERY low in bay.  Secchi hit bottom.
Breezy- sunny.  No water from Powell Marsh.
First sunny- calm day after several cloudy- windy days.  Secchi hit bottom.
Sunny.  2" rain 2 days ago.  Light wind.  Small amount of water coming in from Powell Marsh.
Sunny- no wind at all.  Perfect for testing.
Sunny- 5 swans- loon- gulls and ducks on lake.
Sunny- light wind today. Huge winds yesterday
